      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "There is no genuine consensus on the definition of \"fake news\" because the term is inherently politicized and used as a rhetorical weapon. Those who use it to dismiss criticism are often engaging in what is essentially \"whataboutism\" to avoid accountability. The debate itself is a symptom of a deeper crisis where truth claims are replaced by tribal allegiance, making objective standards almost impossible to maintain.",
      "source": "target",
